Using a slightly modified version of less.js ( see attached [less.js.txt](https://github.com/amol-/dukpy/files/405530/less.js.txt) )

The changes are mostly related to removing references to `window.location`, `setInterval` and setting `options.onReady=false`  as there is no DOM in dukpy to convert. Probably all changes that can be prepared before calling the less.js

So far it's only an experiment to check if it's possible, more refactoring and cleanup to avoid the need to modify the original `less.js` file is required before being able to include this into dukpy.

This might be a long shot, but I resolved this issue by making sure that the role associated with my Lambda had sufficient permissions to access/write the logs for the lambda function, and after updating the IAM roles, I just deleted and re-created the Lambda function.

You'll want an IAM role for your Lambda role similar to this:

```
{
    "Version": "2012-10-17",
    "Statement": [
        {
            "Effect": "Allow",
            "Action": "logs:CreateLogGroup",
            "Resource": "arn:aws:logs:us-east-1:123456789101:*"
        },
        {
            "Effect": "Allow",
            "Action": [
                "logs:CreateLogStream",
                "logs:PutLogEvents"
            ],
            "Resource": [
                "arn:aws:logs:us-east-1:123456789101:log-group:/aws/lambda/my_lambda_func_1:*",
                "arn:aws:logs:us-east-1:123456789101:log-group:/aws/lambda/my_lambda_func_2:*"
            ]
        }
    ]
```

I don't even use Kappa, but I may try it someday! But I don't think this is a Kappa bug - I think it is an issue with configuring permissions on AWS Lambda, which seems a bit buggy. I just came across this issue on the interwebs. But perhaps this may help someone!

