@sebma Yes. This is because `dateutil` currently is essentially a namespace package for the various sub-modules. The reason for this is that each of the sub-modules should be imported lazily as needed. if you only need `dateutil.tz`, you don't necessarily want to have to import `relativedelta` and `parser` as well.

For a while I've been considering a more seamless lazy-load experience that works as users expect it to. I've created issue #771 to track the implementation.

Until then, use `import dateutil.tz` or `from dateutil import tz` when you want to use `dateutil.tz`.

@dansegal1 the Python client library uses `requests` which relies on `urlib3` for making HTTP requests, which mostly is native Python. As for `curl`, it's pure `C` code. So it's pretty hard for  native Python code to beat it here.

